 when they stand before the judgment of God,

526
00:25:12,840 --> 00:25:16,560
 they will actually be exalted by God.

527
00:25:16,560 --> 00:25:19,200
 Jesus is not here to condemn them right now.

528
00:25:19,200 --> 00:25:23,120
 He's inviting them into that ultimate reality.

529
00:25:23,120 --> 00:25:25,240
 I do want to exalt you, my friends,

530
00:25:25,240 --> 00:25:29,720
 but first you do have to humble yourself in this life

531
00:25:29,720 --> 00:25:34,240
 so that one day when I meet you in that final judgment,

532
00:25:34,240 --> 00:25:36,520
 I can exalt you.

533
00:25:36,520 --> 00:25:41,520
 And as Christians, I'm sure we've all heard

534
00:25:41,520 --> 00:25:43,600
 about the virtue of humility,

535
00:25:43,600 --> 00:25:46,640
 but this is the tricky part, church.

536
00:25:46,640 --> 00:25:50,200
 I struggled with that myself as well in my life.

537
00:25:50,200 --> 00:25:54,640
 If we spend the rest of our lives trying to be humble,

538
00:25:54,640 --> 00:25:59,520
 trying to do or say all sorts of things to look humble,

539
00:25:59,520 --> 00:26:02,640
 to sound humble, and at the end of the day,

540
00:26:02,640 --> 00:26:05,520
 oh, we go home, we look at ourselves and say,

541
00:26:05,520 --> 00:26:08,720
 oh, I'm such a humble person today.

542
00:26:08,720 --> 00:26:13,200
 When I talk to Pastor Tim, oh, I was so humble just now.

543
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:17,360
 Oh, when I talk to my friend, oh, I'm such a nice guy.

544
00:26:17,360 --> 00:26:21,520
 I finally achieved humility.

545
00:26:21,520 --> 00:26:26,160
 Oh, so good, right?

546
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:31,160
 That's the voice of pride speaking, right?

547
00:26:31,160 --> 00:26:36,680
 And so let me do read you a paragraph from C.S. Lewis.

548
00:26:36,680 --> 00:26:38,080
 He says this.

549
00:26:38,080 --> 00:26:41,160
 Do not imagine that if you meet a really humble man,

550
00:26:41,160 --> 00:26:44,520
 he will be what most people call humble nowadays.

551
00:26:44,520 --> 00:26:48,880
 He will not be sort of greasy, you know, swarmy person

552
00:26:48,880 --> 00:26:52,440
 who is always telling you that, of course, he's nobody.

553
00:26:52,440 --> 00:26:54,000
 He's not gonna say that to you.

554
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:56,040
 Probably all you will think about him

555
00:26:56,040 --> 00:26:58,800
 is that he seemed a cheerful, intelligent chap

556
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:02,840
 who took a real interest in what you said to him.

557
00:27:02,840 --> 00:27:04,600
 If you do dislike him,

558
00:27:04,600 --> 00:27:08,000
 it will be because you feel a little bit envious of anyone

559
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:10,840
 who seems to enjoy life so easily.

560
00:27:10,840 --> 00:27:14,960
 He will not be thinking about humility.

561
00:27:14,960 --> 00:27:19,560
 Well, in fact, he will not be thinking about himself at all.

562
00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:24,480
 Okay, if anyone, if you need to take picture, do it now.

563
00:27:24,480 --> 00:27:25,480
 I'm gonna move on.

564
00:27:25,480 --> 00:27:29,160
 And there's another pastor, Pastor Rick Warren.

565
00:27:29,160 --> 00:27:31,040
 He said something quite similar,

566
00:27:31,040 --> 00:27:33,640
 which is complimentary to what I read just now.

567
00:27:33,640 --> 00:27:38,200
 He said, "Humility is not thinking less of yourself.

568
00:27:38,200 --> 00:27:41,520
 "It is thinking of yourself less.

569
00:27:41,520 --> 00:27:44,400
 "Humility is thinking more of others.

570
00:27:44,400 --> 00:27:48,280
 "Humble people are so focused on serving others,

571
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:51,440
 "they don't think of themselves."

572
00:27:52,360 --> 00:27:56,360
 And so you see, here's the problem with the Pharisees.

573
00:27:56,360 --> 00:27:58,240
 Yes, they've been trying to obey the law.

574
00:27:58,240 --> 00:28:00,800
 They've been trying to fulfill all these requirements,

575
00:28:00,800 --> 00:28:04,320
 but their focus was still on themselves.

576
00:28:04,320 --> 00:28:08,040
 They thought about themselves too much.

577
00:28:08,040 --> 00:28:11,400
 If we focus solely on ourselves,

578
00:28:11,400 --> 00:28:13,640
 our pursuit of righteousness

579
00:28:13,640 --> 00:28:18,640
 will eventually turn into self-righteousness.

580
00:28:18,640 --> 00:28:20,080
 Let me say that again.

581
00:28:20,080 --> 00:28:22,520
 If we focus solely on ourselves,

582
00:28:22,520 --> 00:28:24,320
 our pursuit of righteousness

583
00:28:24,320 --> 00:28:28,360
 will inevitably lead to self-righteousness.

584
00:28:28,360 --> 00:28:32,200
 I don't know what motivates us to read the Bible,

585
00:28:32,200 --> 00:28:33,960
 to come to church on a Sunday,

586
00:28:33,960 --> 00:28:35,720
 to sing those worship songs,

587
00:28:35,720 --> 00:28:38,960
 to behave like a Christian every day.

588
00:28:38,960 --> 00:28:41,800
 But if we are doing that for ourselves,

589
00:28:41,800 --> 00:28:44,480
 if we're trying to make ourselves feel better,

590
00:28:44,480 --> 00:28:46,960
 that I'm a Christian, so I'm better than,

591
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:48,640
 oh, that person sitting next to me at work,

592
00:28:48,640 --> 00:28:49,480
 he's not a Christian.

593
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:52,080
 You know, he has all these bad habits in life.

594
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:54,960
 I'm a better man than him, and I'm sorry.

595
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:58,720
 Our pursuit of righteousness

596
00:28:58,720 --> 00:29:02,000
 will just turn us into another self-righteous person.

597
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:08,000
 So Jesus actually offered the antidote to pride

598
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:09,120
 in the following.

599
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:11,520
 In the next story, he reads that

600
00:29:11,520 --> 00:29:13,000
 when you give a luncheon or dinner,

601
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:15,040
 do not invite your friends, your brothers or sisters,

602
00:29:15,040 --> 00:29:16,960
 your relatives, your rich neighbors.

603
00:29:16,960 --> 00:29:19,440
 If you do, they may invite you back

604
00:29:19,440 --> 00:29:20,960
 so you will be repaid.

605
00:29:20,960 --> 00:29:23,680
 But when you give a banquet,

606
00:29:23,680 --> 00:29:27,600
 invite the poor, the cripple, the lame, the blind,

607
00:29:27,600 --> 00:29:30,080
 and you will be blessed.

608
00:29:30,080 --> 00:29:31,840
 Although they cannot repay you,

609
00:29:31,840 --> 00:29:36,840
 but you will be repaid at the resurrection of the righteous.

610
00:29:36,840 --> 00:29:41,960
 So we gotta think about others, those around us.

611
00:29:41,960 --> 00:29:47,040
 If you can give without expecting anything in return,

612
00:29:47,040 --> 00:29:51,560
 not even how much praise you will receive because of that.

613
00:29:51,560 --> 00:29:53,880
 If I'm buying someone dinner,

614
00:29:53,880 --> 00:29:56,240
 and I'm expecting that person to go around,

615
00:29:56,240 --> 00:29:58,560
 "Oh, you know, Chapman bought me dinner last night.

616
00:29:58,560 --> 00:30:00,120
 "He's just such a nice person."

617
00:30:00,120 --> 00:30:03,200
 That's what you're getting in return.

618
00:30:03,200 --> 00:30:07,240
 That doesn't count if you do it for nothing in return,

619
00:30:07,240 --> 00:30:11,440
 and you just focus on meeting the needs of others around you,

620
00:30:11,440 --> 00:30:14,720
 serving them wholeheartedly.

621
00:30:14,720 --> 00:30:18,360
 That's humility in God's eyes.

622
00:30:18,360 --> 00:30:21,400
 I remember a couple of years ago,

623
00:30:21,400 --> 00:30:25,120
 before we have this church here in Yuen Long,

624
00:30:25,120 --> 00:30:26,560
 me, Pastor Ivan, Pastor Tim,

625
00:30:26,560 --> 00:30:29,520
 we were all part of the Wan Chai pastoral staff.

626
00:30:29,520 --> 00:30:33,160
 And so we work in Wan Chai every Sunday.

627
00:30:33,160 --> 00:30:37,320
 I remember there was this particular service one Sunday.

628
00:30:37,320 --> 00:30:38,480
 Halfway through the service,

629
00:30:38,480 --> 00:30:40,920
 the preacher has already been preaching,

630
00:30:40,920 --> 00:30:42,680
 speaking on the stage.

631
00:30:42,680 --> 00:30:45,480
 And there was a person walking through the door,

632
00:30:45,480 --> 00:30:50,080
 slowly moving towards the front of the stage,

633
00:30:50,080 --> 00:30:51,440
 to the front row.

634
00:30:51,440 --> 00:30:54,560
 And I can assure you, most of the time in Wan Chai,

635
00:30:54,560 --> 00:30:56,560
 well, like our English services,

636
00:30:56,560 --> 00:30:59,280
 the whole church is just very packed.

637
00:30:59,280 --> 00:31:00,840
 There's no seat at all,

638
00:31:00,840 --> 00:31:03,760
 but he was walking on the front row.

639
00:31:03,760 --> 00:31:05,600
 And later I found out he might have

640
00:31:05,600 --> 00:31:07,640
 a little bit of special needs.

641
00:31:07,640 --> 00:31:09,920
 And as the staff on the roster,

642
00:31:09,920 --> 00:31:13,200
 when I saw that, my first response is,

643
00:31:13,200 --> 00:31:15,360
 oh my gosh, he's disturbing the service.

644
00:31:15,360 --> 00:31:16,480
 I gotta do something.

645
00:31:16,480 --> 00:31:18,000
 Maybe I should bring him somewhere else.

646
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:19,760
 Maybe I should put him to the back.

647
00:31:19,760 --> 00:31:22,080
 I was running all these different scenarios.

648
00:31:22,080 --> 00:31:23,160
 How should I react?

649
00:31:23,160 --> 00:31:26,840
 But luckily, or unluckily, I was actually on the balcony.

650
00:31:26,840 --> 00:31:28,080
 I was so far away from that.

651
00:31:28,080 --> 00:31:30,240
 So I was just mentally, what should I do?

652
00:31:30,240 --> 00:31:33,920
 What would I do if I'm down there in the lower house?

653
00:31:33,920 --> 00:31:36,720
 While I was still thinking about all these,

654
00:31:36,720 --> 00:31:40,360
 that day, Pastor John, our founding pastor,

655
00:31:40,360 --> 00:31:42,040
 he was actually there in the service.

656
00:31:42,040 --> 00:31:43,960
 And he was sitting in the front seat,

657
00:31:43,960 --> 00:31:46,560
 right in the middle on the first row.

658
00:31:46,560 --> 00:31:48,320
 So the next moment, what I saw was,

659
00:31:48,320 --> 00:31:51,200
 as the guy was walking alongside,

660
00:31:51,200 --> 00:31:53,600
 I saw that John actually stood up,

661
00:31:53,600 --> 00:31:58,400
 gently escorting that man to his seat.

662
00:31:58,400 --> 00:32:00,320
 And he quietly walked towards the back

663
00:32:00,320 --> 00:32:01,880
 for the rest of the service.

664
00:32:01,880 --> 00:32:04,880
 And I was watching on the balcony.

665
00:32:04,880 --> 00:32:08,640
 I was telling myself, he is the founding pastor.

666
00:32:08,640 --> 00:32:12,480
 If there's one man who deserves to remain in his seat,

667
00:32:12,480 --> 00:32:13,800
 that would be John.

668
00:32:13,800 --> 00:32:17,920
 And he taught me a lesson that day.

669
00:32:17,920 --> 00:32:23,520
 I look at John, I saw what he did.

670
00:32:23,520 --> 00:32:25,040
 And I was telling myself,

671
00:32:25,040 --> 00:32:30,440
 man, I hope one day when I am his age,

672
00:32:30,440 --> 00:32:32,240
 I could do the same.

673
00:32:32,240 --> 00:32:35,160
 That my heart is not filled with entitlement.

674
00:32:35,160 --> 00:32:37,000
 Well, I'm somebody, somebody,

675
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:39,640
 that somebody else should move away from their seats.

676
00:32:39,640 --> 00:32:40,840
 I should be here.

677
00:32:40,840 --> 00:32:42,600
 Somebody should be giving me their seats,

678
00:32:42,600 --> 00:32:43,920
 not the other way around.

679
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:46,560
 I hope one day when I reach there,

680
00:32:46,560 --> 00:32:49,880
 I could still do that.

681
00:32:49,880 --> 00:32:56,760
 I think sometimes we do feel we're entitled to some things

682
00:32:56,760 --> 00:32:59,360
 because of how much effort we put into

683
00:32:59,360 --> 00:33:00,760
 something of our expertise,

684
00:33:00,760 --> 00:33:03,200
 how good or how much good we've done.

685
00:33:03,200 --> 00:33:05,440
 And we thought we're entitled to something.

686
00:33:05,440 --> 00:33:09,640
 Humility is not thinking less of yourself,

687
00:33:09,640 --> 00:33:12,560
 not thinking, oh, I don't deserve to be seated here.

688
00:33:12,560 --> 00:33:13,680
 It's not like that.

689
00:33:13,680 --> 00:33:16,200
 Humility is not thinking less of yourself.

690
00:33:16,200 --> 00:33:20,960
 Humility is simply thinking of yourself less.

691
00:33:20,960 --> 00:33:22,520
 Think about others.

692
00:33:22,520 --> 00:33:28,360
 I'm wondering today, if you have a seat,

693
00:33:28,360 --> 00:33:30,600
 who can you give that seat to?

694
00:33:30,600 --> 00:33:34,520
 Who would you give up that seat for?

695
00:33:34,520 --> 00:33:37,640
 Is it only someone whom you think

696
00:33:37,640 --> 00:33:39,960
 is more superior than you,

697
00:33:39,960 --> 00:33:42,000
 have a high status than you,

698
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:44,480
 have a better reputation than you,

699
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:47,680
 older than you, look better than you?

700
00:33:47,680 --> 00:33:52,040
 Or you're just gonna give it to someone who is in need?

701
00:33:55,520 --> 00:34:00,520
 What do we want to be known for as a church in our city?

702
00:34:00,520 --> 00:34:05,000
 The Pharisee loves places of honor at feasts

703
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:06,880
 and best seats in the synagogue.

704
00:34:06,880 --> 00:34:09,040
 How about us?

705
00:34:09,040 --> 00:34:14,600
 Do we or can we do the opposite

706
00:34:14,600 --> 00:34:16,920
 by giving the seats to other people,

707
00:34:16,920 --> 00:34:19,920
 the best seats to different people?

708
00:34:19,920 --> 00:34:24,720
 Can we act in a way that communicates to those around us

709
00:34:24,720 --> 00:34:27,320
 that we think they are more important?

710
00:34:27,320 --> 00:34:31,400
 Can we ask God to bring us to a place

711
00:34:31,400 --> 00:34:34,560
 where we think of ourselves less

712
00:34:34,560 --> 00:34:36,080
 and think of others more?

713
00:34:36,080 --> 00:34:42,560
 That's my prayer for myself.

714
00:34:42,560 --> 00:34:45,040
 That's my prayer for my church family.

715
00:34:45,040 --> 00:34:48,640
 I do think that there is a gap

716
00:34:48,640 --> 00:34:50,640
 between what our faith stands for

717
00:34:50,640 --> 00:34:54,480
 and what we're known for in the city right now.

718
00:34:54,480 --> 00:34:56,640
 I do think that gap exists.

719
00:34:56,640 --> 00:35:01,640
 My prayer, my desire is to see that the church

720
00:35:01,640 --> 00:35:03,640
 will have a better reputation here.

721
00:35:03,640 --> 00:35:10,800
 But as the evangelist Moody, he says this,

722
00:35:10,800 --> 00:35:13,120
 "If I take care of my character,

723
00:35:13,120 --> 00:35:17,480
 "my reputation will take care of itself."

724
00:35:17,480 --> 00:35:21,360
 I do think we need to close that gap,

725
00:35:21,360 --> 00:35:24,120
 but that gap is not reputation.

726
00:35:24,800 --> 00:35:27,680
 That gap indeed is character.

727
00:35:27,680 --> 00:35:32,120
 What our faith stands for

728
00:35:32,120 --> 00:35:36,080
 and how we behave what we're known for,

729
00:35:36,080 --> 00:35:37,720
 can we close that gap?

730
00:35:37,720 --> 00:35:41,360
 And don't do it by our own power

731
00:35:41,360 --> 00:35:42,400
 and don't come one day,

732
00:35:42,400 --> 00:35:45,320
 oh, I finally closed that gap, I've done it.

733
00:35:45,320 --> 00:35:50,560
 Let's just think of ourself less.

734
00:35:50,560 --> 00:35:53,040
 Let's think of those around us,

735
00:35:53,040 --> 00:35:57,120
 those in the city more in our everyday life.

736
00:35:57,120 --> 00:36:03,080
 I care deeply about the reputation of our church

737
00:36:03,080 --> 00:36:09,400
 and the church in our city, in our world.

738
00:36:09,400 --> 00:36:12,400
 And we don't need better marketing.

739
00:36:12,400 --> 00:36:14,040
 We don't need better branding.

740
00:36:14,040 --> 00:36:17,000
 We just need to work on our character.

741
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:21,240
 And I need to work on my character.

742
00:36:21,760 --> 00:36:23,880
 (smooches)

743
00:36:23,880 --> 00:36:26,280
 And I believe as we start to do that,

744
00:36:26,280 --> 00:36:29,000
 as we invite the Holy Spirit into our hearts,

745
00:36:29,000 --> 00:36:31,800
 as we work on our character,

746
00:36:31,800 --> 00:36:36,800
 I believe our reputation will start to work on itself.

747
00:36:36,800 --> 00:36:40,480
 My dream is that somewhere in the future,

748
00:36:40,480 --> 00:36:42,240
 maybe in the next generation,

749
00:36:42,240 --> 00:36:44,440
 when my daughters get to go into movies,

750
00:36:44,440 --> 00:36:48,600
 when their portrayal of Christian characters in those movie,

751
00:36:48,600 --> 00:36:52,200
 those characters are not known for being legalistic

752
00:36:52,200 --> 00:36:55,280
 or self-righteous or hypocritic.

753
00:36:55,280 --> 00:37:00,720
 They'll be known for how they long to sacrifice

754
00:37:00,720 --> 00:37:01,800
 for other people.

755
00:37:01,800 --> 00:37:05,200
 They'll be known for their service for other people.

756
00:37:05,200 --> 00:37:09,880
 I long for the day that this is how the world will see

757
00:37:09,880 --> 00:37:12,200
 what they will see in us.

758
00:37:12,200 --> 00:37:15,640
 And this, we cannot control how other people

759
00:37:15,640 --> 00:37:16,600
 see us right now.

760
00:37:16,600 --> 00:37:20,640
 We cannot control how they perceive us because of the past,

761
00:37:20,640 --> 00:37:22,200
 but we can start today.

762
00:37:22,200 --> 00:37:25,680
 We can decide how they will see us tomorrow.

763
00:37:25,680 --> 00:37:29,840
 And I think as we draw close to a parable series,

764
00:37:29,840 --> 00:37:32,000
 as God is calling us into his kingdom,

765
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:34,000
 understanding what it means,

766
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:38,440
 my prayer is that by understanding the parable of Jesus,

767
00:37:38,440 --> 00:37:40,640
 by understanding his heart a little bit more,

768
00:37:40,640 --> 00:37:43,520
 by understanding how he wants to run his kingdom,

769
00:37:44,960 --> 00:37:47,600
 we will start to manifest that kingdom

770
00:37:47,600 --> 00:37:49,080
 in Yuen Long and in our city.

